y="101.5" width="1060" height="10" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="SCVMTBWpLvtzJIhz15lM-6" value="<span>Example arch for a near pure static content delivery arch.<br><br>Data reads only, presenting content to authenticated/authorized users.&nbsp;<br><br>System must be highly performant, less than 1s response times.<br><br>10k-100k users, with various time/availability zones (US-East/West), with spiked bursts of traffic. Users are located 90% in the US, with 10% of user traffic located in Europe (Note: No localization or translating is necessary).<br><br>System will return automotive part information (PartID, Cost, etc. - and may also include various meta-data (BOMs/Assembly info, Similar clients, tracking/logistics, etc.)<br><br>Data is currently housed in on-prem MSSQL structured data (~1Tb), which will need to be ported/migrated to DynamoDBs (NoSQL) for scalability, costing, and availability concerns.<br><br>Additional Concerns:<br>1. Operational Changes:<br><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>- Part Catalog data changes are minimal CRUDs in the DBs and will occur "off-schedule" as a separate content management system.<br><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>- Application changes are monthly releases, and are containerized K8s with Canary and Blue/Green deploys<br><br>2. Security:&nbsp;<br><span style="white-space: pre;">	</span>- All users are required to authenticate into the system (IAM roles, via AWS Cognito management), and are granted various layers of authorization, but typically remain within their respective "client/customer" domains; however, part catalog details are shared across various clients.<br><br>3.&nbsp;<br></span>" div.span:
Example arch for a near pure static content delivery arch.
Data reads only, presenting content to authenticated/authorized users.
System must be highly performant, less than 1s response times.
10k-100k users, with various time/availability zones (US-East/West), with spiked bursts of traffic. Users are located 90% in the US, with 10% of user traffic located in Europe (Note: No localization or translating is necessary).
System will return automotive part information (PartID, Cost, etc. - and may also include various meta-data (BOMs/Assembly info, Similar clients, tracking/logistics, etc.)
Data is currently housed in on-prem MSSQL structured data (~1Tb), which will need to be ported/migrated to DynamoDBs (NoSQL) for scalability, costing, and availability concerns.
Additional Concerns:
1. Operational Changes:
- Part Catalog data changes are minimal CRUDs in the DBs and will occur "off-schedule" as a separate content management system.
- Application changes are monthly releases, and are containerized K8s with Canary and Blue/Green deploys
2. Security:
- All users are required to authenticate into the system (IAM roles, via AWS Cognito management), and are granted various layers of authorization, but typically remain within their respective "client/customer" domains; however, part catalog details are shared across various clients.
3.
